# Always-On Rules — aide

## Workflow Gate

- Identify current stage: Idea, Spec, Implement, Review, QA, Done
- Do not write production code during Spec stage
- Do not skip Review or QA for merged work

## Spec Discipline

- Require approved spec before implementation
- Spec lives in `docs/specs/` or linked issue — create if missing
- Ask user when requirements are ambiguous; do not invent scope

## Documentation First

- Read `docs/project.md` before feature proposals
- Read `docs/architecture.md` before structural changes
- Read `docs/coding-standards.md` before writing code

## Change Control

- Minimal diffs — only modify files required by the task
- No drive-by refactors mixed with feature work
- Architecture changes need ADR in `docs/decisions.md` + approval

## Communication

- State assumptions explicitly
- Present options with trade-offs for ambiguous decisions
- Output structured artifacts per active skill

## Prohibited

- Committing secrets or credentials
- Using `any` in TypeScript without justification
- Deleting tests to make builds pass
- Implementing without referencing an approved spec
